//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// ARM Cortex-A53 IP-XACT 1.4 description
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

This release includes the following level of description as defined by the
IP-XACT specification:

   * Bus interfaces
   * Component model including:
      - RTL view
      - I/O signal interface
      - RTL configuration parameters
   * Memory-mapped register descriptions
   * RTL filesets

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The distribution contains the following components relative to the directory
'logical/cortexa53/ipxact' in the distribution:

 ./README                                                                         : This document
 ./CortexA53_unconfigured.xml                                                     : IP-XACT description of Unconfigured Cortex-A53
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA3/APB/r2p0_0/APB.xml                                      : AMBA Advanced Peripheral Bus (APB 3.0) interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA3/APB/r2p0_0/APB_rtl.xml                                  : AMBA RTL view of the Advanced Peripheral Bus (APB 3.0) interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA3/ATB/r2p0_0/ATB.xml                                      : AMBA Advanced Trace Bus (ATB) interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA3/ATB/r2p0_0/ATB_rtl.xml                                  : AMBA RTL view of the Advanced Trace Bus (ATB) interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA4/ACE/r0p0_0/ACE.xml                                      : AMBA ACE interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA4/ACE/r0p0_0/ACE_rtl.xml                                  : AMBA RTL view of the AMBA ACE interface description
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA4/ACE-Lite/r0p0_0/ACE-Lite.xml                            : AMBA ACE-Lite interface description (referenced by the ACE interface)
 ./busdefs/amba.com/AMBA4/ACE-Lite/r0p0_0/ACE-Lite_rtl.xml                        : AMBA RTL view of the AMBA ACE-Lite interface description (referenced by the ACE interface)
