//---------------------
// Configuration
//---------------------

The component description describes a CortexA53_unconfigured with all possible
features implemented.

Depending on the RTL configuration parameters used, some of these features may
not be present in the configured design. For example, a configuration with no
ACE does not include ACE Interface ports and bus definitions.

To handle the configuration-dependent feature sets, 'ARM presence' vendor
extensions are used in the IP-XACT description which mark when certain features
should or should not be present.  Some tools can interpret these vendor
extensions and allow configuration of the component within the tool.

If your IP-XACT design tool cannot process the ARM vendor extensions, you can
use the provided Build_Component script to generate a new description for a
specific processor configuration.  The 'configured' description has all
configuration options resolved and unimplemented features removed, and does not
contain any ARM vendor extensions.  This description is suitable for using in
any IP-XACT design environment.

For more details about Build_Component, see the section 'Using Build_Component'
below.

//---------------------
// Using Build_Component
//---------------------

The Build_Component script can be used to generate a configured IP-XACT file
from the provided component description. This means that any ARM presence tags
will be used to remove unimplemented features, resulting in an IP-XACT component
file that describes a CortexA53_configured with the specific parameters (see
Configuration above).

The script requires the following tools:
  Perl                     v5.8.8 or above   http://www.perl.org/
  Libxml2                  v2.6.30 or above  http://www.xmlsoft.org/
  XML::LibXML Perl module  v1.70 or above    http://search.cpan.org/dist/XML-LibXML/LibXML.pod

   
   You can run the BuildComponent with a selected configuration by using :  
   
   <RenderCORTEXA53.pl -ipxact> in the following directory <install dir>/logical/cortexa53/verilog/ 
   
   The configuration for rendering IP-XACT will be picked from :
   
   <install dir>/logical/cortexa53/config/CORTEXA53.cfg
   
   and will produce a configured IP-XACT file "CortexA53_configured.xml"

//---------------------
// NOTES
//---------------------

1) The IP-XACT description contains a file set named 'RTL' that
   references generic RAMs and cells in the directories models/rams/generic and
   models/cells/generic respectively and customers can replace 
   with their own implementations.

2) The IP-XACT description includes up to 4 CPUs in the multiprocessor cluster,
   each with its own Debug, PMU, CTI and ETM registers assigned to the Debug APB
   address space.

3) Paths to source files are relative to the directory in which the IP-XACT
   files appear when unpacked into the same directory structure as the bundled
   product deliverables.

